caption.title: Maximum likelihood phylogeny obtained using two novel complete Yellow fever virus sequences plus 126 YFV reference sequences from each different genotype (South American I; South American II; West African; East African).
caption.p: ML showing the two newly genomes belongs to South American I (SA1) genotype. SA2, WAfr, and EAfr indicate the South America II, West Africa, and East Africa genotypes, respectively. The scale bar is in units of substitutions per site (s/s). Node labels indicate bootstrap support values.17DD, the vaccine strain used in Brazil.
